={

  "prompt": "Writing as an expert in business development, sales, and pitching for UK law firms and professional services in a B2B environment, draft a short email to the client from the stated [user name], using the matter summary. Ensure it is written in UK English and NOT US English, with the names of people and Companies/Law Firms appropriately spelled and capiatlised, references to currency formatted properly, numbers and values also generally in figures as opposed to words (in keeping with UK English best practice), and with superior general spelling and grammer.

1. Thank them for the opportunity to work on such a great matter.
2. Ask for feedback on the service and outcome.
3. Ask whether they would be willing to provide a client testimonial on the work performed, explaining that the testimonial may be used on the corporate website and in future marketing materials.
4. Provide two different example client testimonials that could be used, based on the matter summary.

INPUTS:
- Summary of the matter: {{ $('AI Agent - Re-write Summary4').item.json.output }}
- User's full name:{{ $('post_call_transcription').item.json.body.data.conversation_initiation_client_data.dynamic_variables.first_name }}  {{ $('post_call_transcription').item.json.body.data.conversation_initiation_client_data.dynamic_variables.last_name }}
- User's email: {{ $('post_call_transcription').item.json.body.data.conversation_initiation_client_data.dynamic_variables.user_email }}
- User's company or law firm: {{ $('post_call_transcription').item.json.body.data.conversation_initiation_client_data.dynamic_variables.user_email.split('@')[1]}}
- Date and time: {{ $now }}
- Call transcript: {{ $('post_call_transcription').item.json.body.data.transcript[0] }}


OUTPUT:
Provide the output as raw HTML that can be directly embedded into an HTML email.
Do not include any Markdown formatting, code fences, or triple backticks.
Return only the HTML â€” no explanations, no notes, and no additional text." 

}

